   News for Researchers
   Here you can find new items about research opportunities or scientific
   findings.

   Research Services
   Find programs and services for the researcher.

   Research Consortiums
   NIMH Consortia coordinate research, encourage knowledge transfer and
   clinical application of findings and provide research policy
   leadership.

   Literature Alert
   Recent NIMH-supported research articles of interest.

   Research Reports
   Enter here to find publications of professional interest that address
   research on treatment and services, parity, and other priority areas,
   such as neuroscience and prevention research.

   Conference and Workshop Summaries
   Find abstracts, proceedings, and summaries of selected NIMH sponsored
   meetings.

   NIMH Research Web areas
   Web areas focusing on Institute research programs such as AIDS;
   genetics research; mental health services research, neuroinformatics;
   Intramural Research Programs and Technology transfer can be accessed
   here.

   Statistics
   You can find information on the prevalence of mental disorders here.

   *PDF (Portable Document Format) files can be read using Adobe's (TM)
   Acrobat(TM) Reader. This program, which you must install once on your
   computer, allows you to view, navigate and print PDF documents as they
   were published. You will need to download and install a copy of the
   Acrobat Reader in order to use this files. In addition, you can view
   PDF files through your browser by installing the Web browser plug-ins.
   You must install the Acrobat Reader first.

